definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To entangle; to complicate; to involve in knots.
examples: to snarl a skein of thread

definitions.definition: ( transitive ) To place in an embarrassing situation; to ensnare ; to make overly complicated .
( transitive , intransitive ) To be congested in traffic , or to make traffic congested.
To form raised work upon the outer surface of (thin metal ware) by the repercussion of a snarling iron upon the inner surface; to repoussé

definitions.definition: To growl angrily by gnashing or baring the teeth; to gnarl ; to utter grumbling sounds.
To complain angrily; to utter growlingly.
To speak crossly ; to talk in rude, surly terms.
